dcterms:creator: A. B. Chan
N. Vasconcelos
dcterms:description: The UCSD dataset is a small dataset captured from freeway surveillance videos, involving three different traffic densities: sparse, medium, and dense. It includes three classes: truck, car, and bus.
dcterms:title: UCSD dataset

dcterms:creator: J. Li
Y. Zhao
L. Gao
F. Cui
dcterms:description: The mobile robot detection dataset is collected by robot-mounted cameras for fast and lightweight detection algorithms. It includes five classes: red robot, red armor, blue robot, blue armor, and dead robot.
dcterms:title: Mobile robot detection dataset

dcterms:creator: J. Li
Y. Zhao
L. Gao
F. Cui
dcterms:description: The sim2real detection dataset consists of two sub-datasets: a simulation dataset and a real-world dataset, both containing images of robots. The dataset is used to evaluate the transferability of models trained in simulation to real-world scenarios.
dcterms:title: Sim2real detection dataset
